# git workflow

## branches

- the default branch is `main`
- create feature branches with descriptive names for new features
- create bugfix branches with descriptive names for bug fixes

## commits

this project follows conventional commits:

- feat: a new feature
- fix: a bug fix
- docs: documentation changes
- style: formatting, missing semicolons, etc; no code change
- refactor: refactoring production code
- test: adding tests, refactoring tests; no production code change
- chore: updating build tasks, package manager configs, etc; no production code change

examples:
- `feat(product-listing): add pagination support`
- `fix(auth): resolve login redirect issue`
- `docs(readme): update installation instructions`

## pull requests

- create descriptive pull request titles
- provide a detailed description of changes
- link to related issues if applicable
